Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:52.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Did you realize something else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.98,0:02:55.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Literature Era, Editing Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:06.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All the first letters of dialogue are half...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.13,0:03:08.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! You figured out the code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:10.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.27,0:03:12.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:15.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy speaking in Kansai dialect\Nsaid he figured out the code,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.41,0:03:17.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I should call the police here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.41,0:03:19.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}A boy speaking in Kansai dialect?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.01,0:03:22.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.38,0:03:26.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Don't make me repeat myself, idiot! Just get the cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:27.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}C'mon! Don't make me repeat myself, idiot! Just get the cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:31.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hattori-{\i1}kun{\i0}. This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.04,0:03:34.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're already there! It's been awhile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.96,0:03:36.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:43.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The code. I cracked the code hidden in "Halves at the Top."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.73,0:03:48.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I pegged him as an angry old man after I first read his dedication,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.30,0:03:50.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I started to understand as I read
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:56.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that Shinmei-{\i1}han{\i0}'s dialogue in the story was all a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.81,0:03:58.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a code?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:04:05.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. In other words, the dedication wasn't meant to provoke us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.26,0:04:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was askin' someone to find the real message hidden in the novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.21,0:04:16.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I assume you've deciphered the coded message then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.43,0:04:21.17,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yeah. The first part deciphers perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.17,0:04:26.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The key was the novel's title: "Halves of the Top."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:32.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This means the letter at the top of each line is half of a full letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.14,0:04:34.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Half of a full letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.10,0:04:37.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Reading with that in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:39.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with {\i1}chikara{\i0} and {\i1}me{\i0}, you get {\i1}suke{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.07,0:04:41.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with {\i1}jū{\i0} and {\i1}1{\i0} you get {\i1}ke{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:43.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with {\i1}C{\i0} and {\i1}ichi{\i0} you get {\i1}te{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.82,0:04:45.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and at the very end,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.57,0:04:47.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with {\i1}no{\i0} and {\i1}1{\i0} you get a {\i1}re{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.53,0:04:50.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}ku{\i0} and {\i1}hoka{\i0} (other) before it are strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.99,0:04:56.46,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}but if {\i1}hoka{\i0} is meant to be a blank placeholder, you get {\i1}ku{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you read it all together...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.71,0:05:07.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tasu-ke-te-ku-re"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:09.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"{\i1}Tasukete-kure{\i0} (Help us)"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.51,0:05:12.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Help us!" It's an SOS?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.59,0:05:18.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. My guess is he's bein' held somewhere and forced to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:22.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. And that's why he used this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.97,0:05:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He could get a message to his readers\Nwithout his captor noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.20,0:05:32.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom was excited because\Nit's the first new story in 10 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:38.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the perp is a crazed fan or someone\Nplannin' to swipe the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.17,0:05:41.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have these manuscripts been paid for yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.28,0:05:42.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:48.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd tell where to send the money\Nwhen the story was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:51.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Check all suspicious fan letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.16,0:05:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:55.93,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Oh, but I haven't cracked the entire code yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.93,0:05:58.80,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hey! Inspector?! Inspector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:05.38,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hey, Inspector! Hey!\NWhere'd you go?! Quit playing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.38,0:06:11.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Hattori.\NAbout Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s other lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:14.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! If it isn't Kudo! What're you doing there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, I just {\i1}happened{\i0} to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.75,0:06:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I bet! You an' me are a lot alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.32,0:06:22.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We cross paths before we even know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:24.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just get back to the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:30.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You should come to Osaka!\NI'll treat you to some great {\i1}udon{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.23,0:06:33.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand the heavy flavor in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.01,0:06:34.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.57,0:06:36.98,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Sorry! Sorry! The code, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I managed to decipher the first lines of dialogue,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:45.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but "halves at the top"\Ndoesn't fit with the next ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:46.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Put together, you get...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.94,0:06:56.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Watashi hoka ka i he ima i\Nhaku re no tokoro han hito wa."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.87,0:07:01.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you remove the second {\i1}hoka{\i0},\Nonly {\i1}watashi{\i0} makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:05.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He{\i0} and {\i1}ima{\i0} are iffy, but they don't combine into anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:11.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It seems we still don't have all the pieces to this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.04,0:07:16.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There has to be a big piece to this code hidden somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:21.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.19,0:07:23.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.65,0:07:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're there, why should I puzzle over it from so far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.49,0:07:31.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the rest's all yours, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:34.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemme know if you figure anything out! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.12,0:07:40.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That's right! Hattori-{\i1}kun{\i0} should know the rest of the code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:42.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:49.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! He was the one who...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:55.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. This is Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.35,0:07:59.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's forget about the Osaka boy\Nand solve this ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.69,0:08:01.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Good call!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.89,0:08:04.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you feeling sleepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.43,0:08:07.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.76,0:08:12.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know! When you always go,\N"Funya!" or "Hohe!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.00,0:08:14.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, nothing yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.44,0:08:17.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.61,0:08:21.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\c&H3F0000&}Help us! Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.11,0:08:23.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\c&H3F0000&}Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.15,0:08:26.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Dad... Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.38,0:08:31.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'm sure we'll find\Nyour mother and father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.62,0:08:33.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.69,0:08:35.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's use our heads, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:36.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.83,0:08:43.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Damn! Adding or removing\Nnearby letters doesn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:45.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What is this code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.27,0:08:50.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I also don't know who abducted them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.01,0:08:54.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It would be natural to pay close attention to your captive's writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:55.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If the captor is a fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:09:01.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}he'd clearly be suspicious of that\Natypical dedication and character.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.85,0:09:07.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}He would've at least deciphered\Nthe first "help me" by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.22,0:09:09.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}In which case, he'd be after\Nthe manuscript payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:11.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, that can't be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.99,0:09:15.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}You wouldn't hold a person captive\Ntwo whole months for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:21.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I can't figure out the captor's identity {\i1}or{\i0} this code!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.97,0:09:22.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.94,0:09:26.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:31.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Using French to fancy things up is fine,\Nbut don't spell stuff wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.38,0:09:32.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:34.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}French?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.02,0:09:41.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humour" is spelled "h-u-m-o-u-r."\NYou're missing the "h."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.42,0:09:46.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not pronounced, though,\Nso I can understand the mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:53.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That's it! Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:58.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}In which case, the code is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.81,0:10:01.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I can read it! I can read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.01,0:10:04.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I can read every single letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.18,0:10:10.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That's it! That's definitely where\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0} is being held!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:11.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.55,0:10:15.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0} also has dialogue\Nin the eighth chapter we just got!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.93,0:10:17.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.09,0:10:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:28.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Oh no! There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.20,0:10:33.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If we don't hurry, he and his wife will be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:36.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Alright! I'll just do like always...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:40.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and use this Tranquilizer Wristwatch\Nto knock the old guy out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:44.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}. Let me introduce you.\NThis is our chief editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:51.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I-I missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.37,0:11:00.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Whoops! I guess I have no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.17,0:11:03.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! Chief! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.51,0:11:08.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I'll just have to have him play a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.81,0:11:12.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Now to set the Voice-Changing Bowtie to use his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:14.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.55,0:11:17.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait a minute! I don't know what he sounds like!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.12,0:11:22.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, just playing Hide-and-Seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.36,0:11:32.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This is bad! There's only one tranquilizer dart!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:36.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I'll have to wait for them\Nto crack the code themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:37.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:42.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If we don't hurry, Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0} will...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:47.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?! Please wake up, Chief! Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.68,0:11:51.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's snoring. Almost reminds me\Nof "Sleeping Kogoro."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.69,0:11:53.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you laughing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:12:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The chief editor is copying how you sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.06,0:12:04.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems like he has lots of {\i1}humor{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:11.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Humor? As always, you know strange words for a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.14,0:12:14.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those men were talking about it just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.61,0:12:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were saying stuff about "humour"! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:19.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:24.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He misspelled the word, so I fixed it for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:27.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to add the "h."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:29.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.59,0:12:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But French people sure are strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.30,0:12:36.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't read "h" at the start of words!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.27,0:12:40.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If they don't say "h",\Nthey should remove it from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.10,0:12:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Remove it...\N- ...from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.37,0:12:49.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s character lives in France, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.45,0:12:50.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:53.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}. Could this be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.95,0:12:57.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The other key to this code might be the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.95,0:13:02.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that "h" isn't pronounced at the start of words in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.86,0:13:04.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Silent "h"s!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.73,0:13:08.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Characters that start with "h"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.06,0:13:14.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it mean to remove the "h"\Nfrom {\i1}ha{\i0}, {\i1}hi{\i0}, {\i1}hu{\i0}, {\i1}he{\i0}, and {\i1}ho{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.80,0:13:16.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:23.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it means you have to drop the "h" letter when combining letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:26.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the {\i1}hoka{\i0} in the first part works.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:35.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Using all of this to decipher Mr. Shinmei's second scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.44,0:13:37.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}watashi{\i0} and {\i1}hoka{\i0} become {\i1}watashi{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:38.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}i{\i0} and {\i1}ka{\i0} is {\i1}ga{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.02,0:13:40.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then {\i1}he{\i0} and {\i1}ima{\i0} is {\i1}ima{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:42.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then {\i1}i{\i0} and {\i1}haku{\i0} is {\i1}i{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.69,0:13:43.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then {\i1}re{\i0} with {\i1}no{\i0} makes {\i1}ru{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.32,0:13:45.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then {\i1}tokoro{\i0} with {\i1}han{\i0} is {\i1}tokoro{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:48.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then {\i1}hito{\i0} with {\i1}wa{\i0} is {\i1}wa{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:56.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All together, it's "watashi-ga-ima-i-ru-tokoro-wa"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The place I'm at now"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24}watashi ga ima iru-tokoro wa
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.13,0:14:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! It makes a sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.22,0:14:07.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. He used that "wa" instead of "ha" because of the "h" rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.72,0:14:13.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! When you decipher\Nthe third scene he's in, you get...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.35,0:14:19.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ki-to-shi-te-i-ho-te-ru"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.44,0:14:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kido City Hotel? What hotel is that?\NI've never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.74,0:14:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be using Hepburn romanization!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.15,0:14:34.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, {\b0\fnShinGoPro-Medium}ふ{\b\fn} wouldn't be {\i1}hu{\i0}, but {\i1}fu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.32,0:14:38.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you keep the first {\i1}fu{\i0}, it would combine with {\i1}moku{\i0} to make {\i1}hai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.12,0:14:42.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Haido City Hotel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.39,0:14:45.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the fourth set of lines\Nis probably the room number.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:47.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:54.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"2-4-0-7-go-shitsu"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:57.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Room 2407"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:57.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24}2407-go shitsu
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.18,0:15:02.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We go straight to\NHaido City Hotel, Room 2407!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:03.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.01,0:15:04.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.38,0:15:05.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.82,0:15:10.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this manuscript! There's more dialogue!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.52,0:15:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the eighth chapter\Nthat was just faxed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.58,0:15:16.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:18.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Haya-ku{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:25.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ji-kan-ga-nai{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:29.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hurry, there's no time!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:29.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24}hayaku, jikan ga nai
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.27,0:15:49.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haido City Hotel. Follow those police cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:51.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hurry!\N- R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.15,0:15:57.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Dad... Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:02.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Dad! Mom! Please be okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.06,0:16:04.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.79,0:16:07.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's not much time" can also mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:10.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that danger is looming but it's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.83,0:16:16.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been barely an hour since that manuscript was sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.17,0:16:18.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's still the middle of the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.51,0:16:21.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good chance they're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.18,0:16:23.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:32.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But I don't understand what the captor wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:38.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Is a crazed fan anxious for the new\NDetective Samonji series behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:40.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:42.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Was it an abduction to get\Na popular writer's money?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:48.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, Room 2407 is a suite. That doesn't fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:52.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Then what {\i1}is{\i0} the captor after?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.54,0:16:57.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What is the plan of the person\Nwho's forcing Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0} to write
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.34,0:17:00.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}even when he can't sign his own name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.28,0:17:04.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait a minute! If he can't sign his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.15,0:17:08.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}...that means he's dictating his story to someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:11.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Then he's having someone else type it all out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:15.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}even when one misplaced letter\Ncould ruin the code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.46,0:17:18.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.10,0:17:24.64,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Adding and removing for no reason\Nwould make anyone suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:29.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Even if his wife was typing,\Nthe person watching would notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.58,0:17:38.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait! Hold on! Could this incident actually be...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.59,0:17:51.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Room 2407... Alright! This is the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:56.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The captor may have a weapon!\NEveryone stay sharp!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.45,0:18:11.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.09,0:18:12.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:14.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori! Why are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:17.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.29,0:18:20.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeze! Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:34.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:38.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.61,0:18:43.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father passed away just moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.18,0:18:44.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:50.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I called your home many times,\Nbut I couldn't get a hold of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.46,0:18:56.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the one who abducted Mr. Shinmei?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.83,0:18:58.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:03.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my husband's personal physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:05.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who's the kidnapper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.67,0:19:13.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no kidnapper. If there was,\Nit'd be Shinmei himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:16.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Does that mean the code was...?!\N- You can't mean...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.72,0:19:20.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A fabrication put together by my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.69,0:19:24.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.33,0:19:28.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was always saying this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.03,0:19:35.47,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I, of course, feel happiness\Nwhen I receive praise for my works,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:41.04,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}but in my 40 years of writing,\Nthere's a happiness I've yet to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.04,0:19:45.31,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Just once, I'd like to see with my own eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.31,0:19:53.15,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}the face of a reader who solves a\Nmystery before I give the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.15,0:19:58.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he wanted to do so before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:20:04.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so his physician and I helped him write his story here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.13,0:20:06.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Before dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.27,0:20:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He lost use of his arms two weeks ago,\Ndue to terminal cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:15.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why his signatures were copies?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.38,0:20:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for worrying you, Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:25.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father told me not to tell you,\Nto give believability to his code.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:33.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive your father, and consider it\Nhis last selfish act, Kaori...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.59,0:22:12.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about your false alarms...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.83,0:22:18.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely he knew a code like that\Ncould've caused a big police panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.70,0:22:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he always wrote at the end of his novels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:27.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that he wanted to see the proud look of one of his readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.81,0:22:31.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably waiting for a reader who figured everything out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to show up and say, "I solved it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.65,0:22:38.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one ever came.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.22,0:22:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And now that he's gone,\Nthe novel will stay unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.76,0:22:46.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.16,0:22:48.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll write the rest of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.86,0:22:52.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't shame the name Nintaro Shinmei!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.57,0:23:00.01,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Two months after this incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.01,0:23:04.51,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Kaori-{\i1}san{\i0} spectacularly completed her father's novel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.51,0:23:09.95,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and "Halves at the Top"\Nmanaged to become a bestseller!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.95,0:23:14.85,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Naturally, a TV version was soon made\Nand earned great reviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.85,0:23:18.76,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}which led her to enter the writing world!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.76,0:23:24.36,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Although this was because\Nshe was as skilled as her father,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.36,0:23:30.37,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}the dimwitted detective, tomboy girl,\Nand the cheeky boy in glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.37,0:23:36.04,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}who assisted Samonji in the last half of the story also helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.04,0:23:39.18,Narration,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I won't say who they were based on...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:42.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I could do without the "cheeky" part.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.09,0:24:08.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(134,100)\fnSegoe\fscx105\fs28\fsp1\shad0\bord0\alpha&H1F&}NEXT EPISODE
